ipment maintenance solutions and medical technology consulting and advisory solutions the ss segment provides surgical equipment and associated products which include supplemental or peak needs mobile surgical equipment solutions and disposable products andor ancillary equipment universal hospital services inc serves national regional and local acute care hospitals and alternate site providers through direct sales force and websites including uhscom uhssurgicalservicescom and oncaremedicalcom the company was founded in  and is based in minneapolis minnesota universal hospital services inc is a subsidiary of uhs holdco inc detailed description  west th streetsuite minneapolis mn united statesfounded in  employees phone  fax  wwwuhscom key executives for universal hospital services inc mr thomas j leonard chief executive officer and director age  mr kevin e ketzel president age  mr david e dovenberg chairman emeritus and advisor of audit committee age  mr james b pekarek chief financial officer and executive vice president age  mr scott a christensen chief accounting officer vice president and controller age  compensation as of fiscal year  universal hospital services inc key developments universal hospital services inc reports earnings results for the first quarter ended march   reaffirms earnings guidance for the full year of  may   universal hospital services inc reported earnings results for the first quarter ended march   for the quarter the company’s total revenues were  million representing a  million or  increase from total revenues of  million for the same period of  adjusted ebitda for the three months ended march   was  million a  million or  increase from adjusted ebitda of  million for the same period of  net loss attributable to the company was  million compared to  million a year ago the company reaffirmed its earnings guidance for the full year of  for the period the company expects adjusted ebitda of  million to  million and accrual capex of  million 